{# Voting Access by State - All 11 Former Confederate States #}
<div class="impact-grid">
  {% for card in impactCards %}
    <article class="impact-card{% if card.expanded %} impact-card--expanded{% endif %}{% if card.postShelby %} impact-card--post-shelby{% endif %}">
      <header class="impact-card__header">
        <span class="impact-card__abbr">{{ card.abbr }}</span>
        <h3 class="impact-card__title">{{ card.title }}</h3>
        {% if card.postShelby %}
          <span class="impact-card__badge">Post-Shelby</span>
        {% endif %}
        {% if card.expanded %}
          <span class="impact-card__badge impact-card__badge--expanded">Expanded Access</span>
        {% endif %}
      </header>
      <div class="impact-card__stat">{{ card.stat }}</div>
      <p class="impact-card__content">{{ card.content }}</p>
      <footer class="impact-card__footer">
        <a href="{{ card.sourceUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="impact-card__source">
          {{ card.source }} â†’
        </a>
      </footer>
    </article>
  {% endfor %}
</div>
<p class="impact-summary">
  <strong>The pattern:</strong> Of the 11 former Confederate states, 8 enacted new voting restrictions after <em>Shelby County v. Holder</em> (2013) removed federal preclearance requirements. Only Virginia expanded access, and only Virginia voted Democratic in 2024.
</p>
